<b>Treatments</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Under normal circumstances, a dose of antiepileptic medicines could be very helpful in controlling seizures, depending on the trigger that caused it. But doctors will also give you a combination of these medicines in order to treat you better. However, if your condition is a little severe, epilepsy surgery is also available.</span>

<b>Going beyond in the holistic approach</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Louise Hay, motivational leader and empowerment coach who has done path breaking work in supporting HIV/AIDS patients and their families, has said that, â€œIllness however mild or severe is an indicator of your emotional state, caused by your thoughts and focus.â€ </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to her, the main cause of epilepsy is: </span><b>Sense of persecution. Rejection of life. A feeling of great struggle. Self-violence.</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">One way of healing this is through saying or writing affirmations. Doing this regularly can help to reduce the debilitating effects of this illness. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Her affirmation for treating epilepsy is: </span><b>I choose to see life as external and joyous. I am eternal and joyous and at peace. </b>";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"0";}}